      "language": "sanskrit",
      "summary": "The *Vedānta-Kaustubha* is Śrīnivāsa's *vyākhyā* on Nimbārka's *Vedānta-Pārijāta-Saurabha* and the canonical sub-commentary of the Sanaka-sampradāya. Where Nimbārka's bhāṣya is famously terse, the *Kaustubha* opens out the doctrinal *prameyas*: it explicates the *svābhāvika* — intrinsic, unconditioned — character of both *bheda* and *abheda* between Brahman, *cit*, and *acit*; it stages the *pūrvapakṣa* against *māyā-vāda* and *aupādhika-bhedābheda* and supplies the *uttarapakṣa* the founding bhāṣya only gestures at; and it elaborates the *aṃśa-aṃśin* relation by which *jīvas* are eternally portion-and-whole of Brahman without merger or severance. The work also clarifies the school's Vaiṣṇava theological commitments — Kṛṣṇa with Rādhā as *parabrahman*, *prapatti* and *bhakti* as the means of liberation — and supplies the structural template that Keśava-Kāśmīrī's *Kaustubha-Prabhā* will subsequently sub-comment in turn. It is, in effect, the operative doctrinal text of the Nimbārka-line tradition.",
